{"title_page": "Orya Maqbool Jan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Orya Maqbool Jan\n| image              =\n| birth_date         = \n| alma_mater         = \n| birth_place        = [[Gujrat City|Gujrat]], [[Punjab, Pakistan]]\n| residence          = \n| nationality        = Pakistani\n| education          = \n| occupation         = [[Civil servant]], columnist\n| years active       = \n| organization       = Al Ilm Trust\n| television         = Harf E Raaz\n| relatives          = \n| awards             =\n| website            = http://www.alilmtrust.com\n[https://web.archive.org/web/20180118073526/http://orya.pk/ Official website]\n}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| channel_direct_url = channel/UC8jWGeUHBDg6Vbq1rICVwBA\n| channel_display_name = Orya Maqbool Jan\n| subscribers        = 3.1 lac subscribers\n| subscriber_date    = March 2020\n| views              = \n| view_date          = \n| years_active       = 2018\u2013present\n| silver_button      = yes\n| silver_year        = 2019\n| stats_update       = 31 August 2019\n}}\n'''Orya Maqbool Jan''' (<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"ltr\">\u0627\u0648\u0631\u06cc\u0627 \u0645\u0642\u0628\u0648\u0644)</span> is a Pakistani anti-secular<ref>{{cite news |title=Pakistani school drops John Lennon\u2019s Imagine from concert after protest |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/pakistani-school-drops-john-lennon-s-imagine-from-concert-after-protest/story-NDm8TvtsUN81nLyQy5ooTL.html |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=Hindustan Times |date=25 August 2017 |language=en}}</ref> [[columnist]], and former civil servant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/28-Apr-2019/in-support-of-vaccinations|title=In support of vaccinations|date=27 April 2019|website=The Nation}}</ref><ref name=\"dunyanews1\">{{Cite web|url=http://blogs.dunyanews.tv/17148/|title=Our nation has been plagued by one poisonous scholar after the other|date=17 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1411347|title=PTI leaders in a quandary over Orya Maqbool Jan's nomination for Punjab caretaker CM |work=Dawn |first=Arif |last=Malik |date=1 June 2018}}</ref> He is also a user of [[YouTube]], and his channel has more than 100,000 subscribers. He is known for his various conspiracy theories including [[9/11 conspiracy theories|9/11 conspiracy]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2018/06/02/six-times-orya-maqbool-jan-proved-he-is-the-ultimate-misogynist/ |title=Six times Orya Maqbool Jan proved he is the ultimate misogynist - Pakistan Today|website=www.pakistantoday.com.pk}}</ref> He appears currently as an analyst on [[Neo News]] show ''Harf e Raaz''.\n\nJan previously worked as civil servant and after retirement joined journalism.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Notezai|first1=Muhammad Akbar|title=Why is Balochistan in love with Orya Maqbool Jan?|url=http://nation.com.pk/21-May-2016/why-is-balochistan-in-love-with-orya-maqbool-jan|accessdate=2 December 2017|work=[[The Nation (Pakistan)]]|date=21 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chaudhry|first1=Kashif|title=Challenging Orya Maqbool Jan and Ansar Abbasi|url=http://nation.com.pk/25-Jun-2016/challenging-orya-maqbool-jan-and-ansar-abbasi|accessdate=2 December 2017|work=[[The Nation (Pakistan)]]|date=25 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Hussain|first1=Shujaat|title=Orya Maqbool Jan's hysterics are creating an atmosphere of fear among the teaching community|url=http://nation.com.pk/24-Jun-2016/orya-maqbook-jan-s-hysterics-are-creating-an-atmosphere-of-fear-among-the-teaching-community|accessdate=2 December 2017|work=[[The Nation (Pakistan)]]|date=24 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Hamdani|first1=Yasser Latif|title=Orya Maqbool Jan's attack on Jinnah|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/106254/orya-maqbool-jans-attack-on-jinnah/|accessdate=2 December 2017|work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)]]|date=12 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=TTP considering Ansar Abbasi, Orya Maqbool Jan as negotiators|url=https://www.geo.tv/latest/91921-ttp-considering-ansar-abbasi-orya-maqbool-jan-as-negotiators|accessdate=2 December 2017|work=[[Geo News]]|agency=AFP|date=3 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Banned from Norway==\nIn 2018 he was banned from visiting Norway after a video of his was seen where he tell truth about the Ahmadis, qadeyani and his remarks about Jews.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2018/10/26/norway-rejects-orya-maqbools-visa-for-hate-speech/|title=VIDEO: Norway rejects Orya Maqbool's visa for 'hate speech' - Pakistan Today|website=www.pakistantoday.com.pk}}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n*''Girdb\u0101d : Balocist\u0101n ke qab\u0101'il\u012b pas man\u1e93ar men\u0332 likh\u0101 gay\u0101 \u1e0dr\u0101mah'', Quetta : Zumurrud  Publications, 1996, 308 p. <small>A play on socio-cultural problems with particular reference to the Baloch tribes in Pakistan.</small>\n*''\u1e24arf-i r\u0101z'', Lahore : Sang-e-Meel Publications, 2005-2013, 1616 p. (in 5 volumes). <small>Essays on deteriorating political conditions in Pakistan.</small>\n*''Q\u0101mat : sh\u0101\u02bbir\u012b'', Lahore : Sang-e-Meel Publications, 2011, 144 p. <small>Urdu poetry.</small>\n*''Mujhe hai \u1e25ukm-i az\u0332\u0101n\u0332 : Z\u0324arb-i-mu\u02bcmin sh\u0101\u02bci\u02bb hone v\u0101le k\u0101lam'', Lahore : Ilm-o-Irfan Publishers, 2012, 336 p. <small>Author's collected columns on various international political issues, published in weekly ''Z\u0324arb-i mu\u02bcmin'' Karachi during 2004-06.</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jan, Orya Maqbool}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Pseudohistorians]]\n[[Category:Pakistani conspiracy theorists]]\n[[Category:Pakistani Islamists]]\n[[Category:Pakistani poets]]\n[[Category:Pakistani dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Critics of Ahmadiyya]]\n[[Category:Male critics of feminism]]\n[[Category:Critics